iences directly, nurture relationships, and drive measurable results.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Do you provide the tools, or must I have my own platform?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-email-2&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<\/p>\n<p>We\u2019re flexible. If you already have an email platform like Mailchimp, HubSpot, or Klaviyo, we can work with it. If you don\u2019t, we help you choose the right one for your business needs and budget. For SMEs, Mailchimp or Brevo may be the most cost-effective. For e-commerce, Klaviyo is usually best because of its WooCommerce and Shopify integrations. For corporates or B2B, HubSpot is ideal because it doubles as a CRM. We handle everything from account setup to full integration.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Can you integrate email with my CRM or e-commerce store?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-email-3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<\/p>\n<p>Yes. We specialise in seamless integrations. For e-commerce stores in Kenya running on WooCommerce or Shopify, we connect email platforms like Klaviyo or Mailchimp so customer behaviour (like abandoned carts or product views) automatically triggers personalised emails. For corporates and NGOs, we integrate with CRMs such as Salesforce, Zoho, or HubSpot to align email campaigns with sales or donor management workflows. This ensures your email marketing is not a standalone channel but part of your overall business system.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;How often should I send campaigns?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-email-4&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<\/p>\n<p>It depends on your industry and audience, but consistency matters more than frequency. For e-commerce brands, we recommend weekly campaigns supplemented by automated flows like abandoned cart reminders. NGOs often succeed with monthly newsletters plus segmented donor updates. Corporates might opt for quarterly reports alongside more frequent client updates. The key is to send enough to stay relevant without overwhelming your audience. A good baseline is one to four campaigns per month, adjusted after reviewing engagement metrics.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Can you handle both design and content?&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;faq-email-5&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<\/p>\n<p>Yes. We provide end-to-end email marketing services. Our in-house creative team designs branded, mobile-optimised templates, while our copywriters craft persuasive content tailored to your audience. This includes subject lines optimised for open rates, body copy focused on conversions, and CTAs that drive action. For NGOs, this might mean storytelling emails that highlight impact; for e-commerce, product-driven campaigns; for corporates, professional updates. You don\u2019t need to outsource design or copy separately\u2014we manage the entire process for you.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][\/vc_tta_accordion][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; content_placement=&#8221;middle&#8221; type=&#8221;vc_default&#8221; margin_top=&#8221;5&#8243; margin_bottom=&#8221;10&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1716548610536{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_single_image image=&#8221;6172&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221; alignment=&#8221;center&#8221; css=&#8221;&#8221; lazy_loading=&#8221;true&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;] Why Email Marketing Still Works in 2025 Despite the rise of social media, influencer platforms, and messaging apps, email remains one of the most cost-effective and reliable marketing channels. Global research shows that email marketing generates an average&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"